fields.description: We're seeing it everywhere -- tuft love. This piece brings glitz and glamour to a space. Inspired by old hollywood, it has Swarovski Crystal Buttons. Fantastic without being over the top.

A pair of Chinese guardian lions. They have traditionally stood in front of Chinese imperial palaces, tombs, or houses of the wealthy. Perfect for a bookcase or table in your own palace. They're very striking in copper.

These bar stools are similar in look to the kong counter stool from Emeco (and here, not even a fraction of the price). That stool was intended to make it easy and graceful for the super model clientele to slither in and out of the bar. The more you know....
1970s Lucite Coffee Table by Charles Hollis Jones. In great condition for it’s age, very light signs of use, no crazying.

A circa 1950s Eames for Herman Miller fiberglass rocker in a Lemon Yellow color.
It’s all original, there are no labels or stamps
But this is a Herman Miller one.
Very good condition over all, does have a crack, which is possible to fix if wanted at a boat repair shop.
It a wonderful vintage example of their work.

1970s MOD bentwood ceiling fixture.
10in x 9in, with a very long swag cord.
Very nice condition, light signs of wear/use

The Wassily Chair, also known as the Model B3 chair, was designed by Marcel Breuer in 1925. The handlebar of a bike inspired the use of steel tubing to build the chair. This was revolutionary at the time since the process for making seamless steel tubing had only recently been developed. Previously, steel tubing had a welded seam, which would collapse when the tubing was bent. See, you learn something every day.
Capiz ball swag lamp. Great vintage condition over all with no cracks or breaks to the capiz.
Mid-century Dowel Console Table circa 1970s, that also could work as a desk. In great shape over all, just light signs of normal wear.

1970's frosted white globe held up by a curvy chrome arm, all standing on a round metal base. Over all in great shape, light signs of normal wear. Globe does have a few minor scuff marks. To the moon, Alice.. To the moon.
There's nothing like the handsome design of the classic pharmacy table lamp. The brass finish is quite alluring. It brings to mind adjectives such as solid, rich, and inviting.

Stunning circa 19th century Chinese four panel screen, this hand carved 4 panel screen has images of warriors, elders, family scenes, one quite unusual with a mother and child and a man and his horse. Gilded on one side, with red paint on the other. May have been from an opium bed. A wonderful and unique piece from the past.
Very good condition, Structurally sound, there is some minor loss of gold to the edges of the large center panels as well as a few small scratches to the wood on the back side. The high relief carvings are in tact.

Two words come to mind: laid back. This Fritz Hansen Lounge Chair System 123 Model E (sounds like a souped up car, doesn't it?) is from Denmark. Made of Black Wool and a sturdy steel frame. In very good condition

Classic Eames design, the 670 lounge chair and 671 ottoman for Herman Miller.
Rosewood paneled and black leather upholstery, ottoman is stamp 1979
Great shape over all for its age, light signs of normal wear.

John Keal for Brown Saltman Mahogany Sideboard
Two cabinets, with two shelves, four drawers, not shown in photos all the way on it’s bottom there’s a
long cabinet that would hold the table’s leaves.
Condition, fair/good. Great bones, would need to be refinished to really bring out it’s beauty.
Made with navy Irish linen, this item has a beautiful goldenrod applique and magenta trim. Adds style to most any living room.

These occasional tables, designed by Ayush Kasliwal, in hand-turned ebonized Beech wood or Teak, combine traditional ornamented furniture elements, deconstructs them, and recombines them in a contemporary form.
One-of-a-Kind white washed wood chest by John Dickinson, circa 1970
Angular, repurposed steel stacking chairs by artist Doug Meyer
Custom ottoman designed by Jeffers Design Group with indigo linen fabric & viscose/silk embroidered geometric trim detail. This piece has a bit of that southwestern flavor to it.
Vintage painted metal side table... for that shabby chic look.
What's better than ricotta? Terra cotta. We love this ode to the ladies.
Vintage brass cow skull with horns. Versatile as either wall or table decor. Show them that you're not going to take any bull, cowboy.

Wefts of horsehair are combined with brass and etched glass, implying a structural weight bearing function for the coarse hair. Pretty funky!

Lamping: 2 Type A T10 bulbs. Max 60W each. 25W bulbs included. All pieces made to order.
If you're going to get double crossed, we hope it is because you got this lamp. Black glaze with harness detail, don't worry it's a chic and trustworthy piece.

It's all about geometry. or was it trigonometry? These fixtures are a study in repeating triangular and conical shapes. Made with blackened brass and hand cast porcelain cones to emit a delicate glow. Made to order.

This Mitchell Black piece fits in with our philosophy --- make a nod to the past, but focus on the present. This is a beautiful mix of traditional art and contemporary style. Used as table or wall art, this piece has an acrylic frame with brushed aluminum standoffs.

Striking like sunset in the Arizona desert. Each piece is dyed, painted, and printed by hand. This is art that you can interact with, objects that function while bringing style and warmth into any room. Proudly made in Los Angeles by Rule of Three.
Picture frame from Alexandra Von Furstenberg, the queen of acrylic decor. Place your photo between the two sheets of acrylic and then snap them together. What a snap to use!
You don't have to be a mad scientist to love this cluster vase. Made from an assemblage of smaller bottles, this piece allows you to emphasize the beauty of each flower.
A beautifully hand-crafted queen bed build from sustainably harvested and reclaimed woods, so every piece is one of a kind. Bring character to your bedroom, using this piece as a natural focal point.
This hand-crafted piece was built from exotic demolition hardwoods. It features a patchwork surface, balancing urban aesthetic with sustainable design. You can't get cooler than that.
This is an update on midcentury modern, with tailored box cushions and slim, tapered legs... and if you haven't gotten the memo yet, midcentury modern is so in.
A beautiful mix of iron and steel that features an antique nickel finish.
With its rounded high back and swiveling base, have you ever seen anything so smooth? Only a limited amount in stock.
Built from reclaimed pine and accented with a cool blue tone, this is definitely not run of the mill.
Sleep in style in this Art Deco inspired bed. Sleek, linear design married with modern upholstery details makes this a perfect piece for any contemporary bedroom.
Simple yet sophisticated, this full trundle bed will bring a modern aesthetic and distinct style to your bedroom.
Made from vintage textile spools, this wine rack's a showstopper.

The Bihar reminds us of our travels to India, the beautiful colors and hand block printed fabrics. However, these headboards are handmade by craftman in the USA. But, they'll still inspire you to dream about your future travels.
Inspired by a european design from the 1960's, this handwoven chair is rustic yet chic. (Note: decorating your space in all things wood is not required).
Don't be square. This handsome hexagon-shaped table is made from a solid chunk of mango wood. The top is covered in antique brass foil to create a subtle contrast in color and texture.
Standard design with a splash of personality. Now, just cue up a rerun of ER for the full Clooney experience.
A perfect antique style linen cabinet made with reclaimed wood and iron. Great for creating an old rustic charm into your home decor.
Combines modern functionality with woods reclaimed from former buildings. (oh, If that wood could talk, the stories it would tell). Anyway can't you just picture this in a designer loft in Brooklyn?

Artist Dana Hemenway takes macrame to a whole new level with these limited edition woven extension cord lights. These unique pieces are visually playful. They add a pop to any room.

Available in custom colors and lengths. These are made to order.
If you're looking for a traditional yet unique statement piece, search no more. This beaded chandelier features impressive metalwork design in its intricate cascades of iron chains. So classy.

Whimsical and oh so fantastical. This is what fairy tales are made of... or maybe what eco-friendly homes are made of. Regardless, remember it's okay to have a few daring pieces. It's all about how you put it together.
Add an edge to your minimalistic aesthetic. Note: no animal was harmed in the making of this lamp.

Individual hand-cut capiz shells are edged in silver metal and assembled like a stained-glass window to create these blooming lotus chandeliers. 

If you're interested in the small diameter (13") or large (21"), please contact us.

Inspired by the colors of India, but handmade in the USA. This headboard has the rhythmic shapes and hand block printed fabrics that will keep you dreaming of far away lands.


headboard: 18"'d x 41"w x 70"h, side rails: 9"d x 76"w x 39.25"h
queen: 88"d x 76"w x 37"h, king: 89"d x 93"w x 37"h
Classic comfort. This winged loveseat has gently curving arms, which give it an elegant sensability. This is a forever piece that can be 'dressed' to meet any occasion.
Pop a cork with this slyly patriotic Uncle Sam Corkscrew. With a bottle opener at the base and a hand-pulled corkscrew under the barrel. You sly dog, you.
Simple and striking, just like a peacock. This rug has a contemporary flair. It's 100% hand tufted and dyed wool. It'll add an accent of color to any drab room.
This is an eye-catching piece is one of our favorites. The combination of the lion's feet and the coil brings so much character to a room. So, at only 24 inches tall, it carries so much stature.

This is an absolute beauty! The color of the leather is so rich, we can almost taste it. Picture this wingback next to the window in your study. Don't you just think masterpiece theater? Time to pull out the cigar pipe and your velvet slippers.
This piece reminds us of the wooden toy pianos they used to make. We love it and it's unique structure. You don't have to live in a concert hall for it to fit in.
Cherry-shaped, this tufted leather chair is a stand out piece. Don't you love it? Yeah, we know the pickings are good.

Yes kiddies, once upon a time you had to pull out a drawer and look through index cards to find a book in the library. Seems worlds away. Well, this amazing piece can stand as a relic from the past or with a little love, you can breathe new life into these vintage library drawers.

Color, color, everywhere! We fell in love with this piece because of its rich purple upholstery. This vintage fiberglass shell chair by Charles and Ray Eames with the original Knoll upholstery and a new rocking chair base.

Great condition with minor age appropriate wear.

This is a Mid-Century Modern lounge chair designed by Milo Baughman for Thayer Coggin that reclines and can be used in three positions.  This chair has been professionally reupholstered in blue leather. Great condition with vintage wear on the frame.
This is a pair of Mid-Century Modern lounge chairs in the style of Milo Baughman.  They have chrome frames and have been professionally reupholstered.

"If you look at these chairs, they are mainly made of air, like sculpture.  Space passes right through them."

This is an early Mid-Century Modern 'Bird' Chair by Harry Bertoia for Knoll. Great condition with age appropriate wear.  

Ottoman is 23.5"W x 17"deep x 14.5"H

This Mid-Century Modern rocking chair was designed by Mitsumasa Sugasawa for Tendo Mokko in 1966.  It has a bent wood frame and the original black naugahyde upholstery.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, one small nick in the upholstery on the top edge.

This is a pair of rare Mid-Century Modern swivel lounge chairs by George Mulhauser for Plycraft. They have curved rosewood frames and black naugahyde upholstery.

Great condition with some vintage wear along the bottom edge of the wood frames and vintage patina on the upholstery (one small tear on the back of one of the arms).

This is a CH 34 lounge chair designed by Hans Wegner for Carl Hansen & Son in 1959. This chair was presented at 'Købestævnet' in Fredericia in 1959 and was in production from 1959-1964. It has a teak frame and the original black leather upholstery.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, such as scratches on the wood frame and distressed leather.

This is a pair of vintage Mid-Century bent wood lounge chairs with newly upholstered black leather cushions.

Great condition with age appropriate wear on the wood frames such as scratches.

This is a vintage Mid-Century 'Propeller' coffee table by Knut Hesterberg for Ronald Schmitt in 1964. It has a aluminum 'propeller' base with a gold finish and a round glass top.

Great condition with age appropriate wear such as scratches.

This is a vintage studio craft table by Napa artist, Dane Newcomb.  It is solid walnut and oak with stunning lines and details.

Great condition.

This is a pair of Mid-Century Modern brutalist end tables by Lane.

Great condition with age appropriate wear, such as some small nicks.  See images.

Eye-popping in red and white! This vintage Mid-Century dresser has six drawers (two deep drawers on the bottom). This design was created in 1968 by Raymond Loewy for his DF2000 series X-line.

Great condition with vintage wear.
The bed frame that attaches to the headboard is 64.5"W x 82"L, and the inside storage compartment in the headboard is 63"L x 11"H x 14"deep.

Frank Lloyd Wright?! Designed in 1936 for the S.C. Johnson Company's Administrative Building in Wisconsin. The rights were given to Cassina to produce it in 1985 (it's no longer manufactured). This desk is marked Cassina #0147, Frank Lloyd Wright. It has three cherry wood tops positioned at different heights and a 'brick red' painted tubular steel frame. It includes two drawers and a removable waste basket and two storage racks. It also has polished brass accents. The desk top is 30"H (26"H to bottom shelf).

Great condition with age appropriate wear such as scratches.
Vintage Oak Articulated lamp. 15-30"L arm

This is a vintage 'Orbiter' floor lamp designed by Robert Sonneman. The 5.5"diameter shade, the arc, and the 34"L arm can tilt and turn.

Great condition with minor vintage wear such as a few small scratches.

This is a vintage industrial wall mount steel task lamp. The wall bracket is stamped "ARTISTIC LAMP NY". Edison bulb is included.

Great condition with age appropriate wear.
How cool is this? A vintage Mid-Century acrylic Nixie tube clock. Great condition. Makes you think of Macgyver doesn't it?

Moody. Screaming to be touched. We love the industrial look and we're not alone. The style popped out of nowhere a few years back and continues to be strong. So, if you're looking for a nice piece from this category, this table lamp is a great place to start.
Your home office deserves more than a standard office chair. This wood desk chair brings a bit of character. So, if you have to work from home, at least work in style.

Yes kids, we used to have to look through a drawer of index cards to find a book in the library. Wow, have times changed. As is, this piece is a beautiful relic of the past. With a little attention, it can find new purpose.
Oversized

Burnt sienna. That's the color in the crayola box that comes to mind. Now, just imagine pairing these chairs with a creme-colored shag rug. Add a warm fire place in the background. Don't stop there. Build that cozy sitting room you've been talking about.
Classy and dripping of elegance, this is our kind of crystal ball. It makes us see ballrooms, ball gowns, and dream of time gone by. A gorgeous pick (2 available).
These boots were made for walking... or for lighting up a room. This lamp is just fun, adding personality to a room. Add a lamp shade to dress it up or dress it down.
Stunning marble-top boomerang-shaped midcentury cocktail table with top in bright white with shades of gray and taupe veining.

Artist and inventor Mark Weinstein of Saint Louis Missouri, established Marc Creates Inc. in 1967. His vintage, multi-dimensional metal sculptures can be found across the world. We think of this piece as the tree that lives year round.

c. 1680 (back)

with storage under seat
Oak and Douglas Fir wood construction Circa 1910
Solid, quarter-sawn oak, hand-carved cabinet with wrought iron hardware. How ornate? How gorgeous. How stately? How could this piece not have been owned by kings?

Antique Indonesian carved teak chest with secret compartment- small door in top with iron latches, and smaller door down below to the secret compartment. Covered in lovely detail of carved rosettes. Imagine the things that this chest has seen and the secrets it has hidden.

This loveseat looks so lux, with it's deep maroon color and beautiful tufts. We love the scalloped bottom and the fact that it is armless. It'll be a treasure to style and it's definitely a steal at this price.
One of nature's strongest woods takes on its toughest task yet, caring for your special reserve. Who would've guessed that teak was so strong based on the sleek figure of this beautiful wine rack.
Make coffee time special! These are a modern and unique take on the conventional coffee spoon. Remember, just like fashion, it's important to accessorize if you want to show your style.

Made from reclaimed driftwood that's been sanded, stained, and shellacked. All wood is salvaged from Lake Eerie (which is stamped on the brass, a good conversation starter). Basically, it's a cool way to open a cool beverage.
This striking, 3 drawer accent chest is crafted out of bone. It truly could be considered a work of art.

The Componibili was introduced by Italian furniture maker Kartell in 1969. The system has been in production now for 40 years, and is a part of the permanent collection of New York's Museum of Modern art. It's versatile and flexible. Popular as beside tables, but also useful in the bathroom, home office, kids' rooms, or pretty much wherever you need storage.
These chairs are gems, with their vibrant orange upholstery. You just have to know how to style them. You're one step away from creating the 'Mad Men' look.

This is a super classy two tier tray, originally from Williams-Sonoma. Use it as a classic bar tray to display your favorite bottle of Patron or as a side table to place some reading. Black and brass, the color combination makes it a nice accent to any room.
We love this couch because it just looks so sharp. Made of a white wood frame with blue fabric cushions, it's a good catch.

Glam, glam, glam. This gold metal brass side table has two smoked glass shelves. The top level rotates and has a  shiny finish. Good condition given age and use. Circa 1975 with very faint light scratches.

Rare MCM Drexel Esperanto style wood cane chair with cane intact. In excellent condition with minor chips, scratches, and wear to original wood finish. Upholstery is in great condition and it is a very comfortable piece of mid-century art. Great candidate for a new coat of fresh lacquer. Circa 1958.

The highly detailed carved legs with ball feet are eye catching on this vintage square table (with natural wood top and skirt). Very unique table with unknown origins. Beautiful patina to wood estimated to be circa 1920.

Roberto foschia sphera egg stool. Made in Friuli, Italy, this designer bar stool is a model in design study. It's a great piece and perfect for mixing and matching if you're going for an eclectic look.
Great condition. Some scuffing. Tested & working. One rubber foot missing.
1970s Lightolier Space Age era melamine lamp with a solid cream shade, a vivid tangerine orange body and a simple on off switch at the base.
fields.color_description: solid cream shade and vivid tangerine body

fields.description: We've gone bananas over this vintage ceramic mug from the San Diego Wild Animal Park featuring their famous Lowland Gorilla "Trib". Retro chic.
fields.short_name: 1970's San Diego Wild Animal Park Mug

fields.description: Handcrafted from Repurposed Oak chairs and finished with Teak oil. This unique piece has its roots in Wayland, NY 1939.
Repurposed push mower and car leaf springs, reclaimed oak flooring and rocker arms. Wood Finished with Teak oil, metal finished with satin clear coat.

Cast in solid brass and polished to perfection by hand. Like a fine wine or your favorite leather jacket, brass only gets better with age. Over time, the polished brass will develop a rich natural patina.
Handcrafted twinkle meets Park Avenue luxury. Sand-cast in solid brass and polished to perfection by hand, these Brass Muse Napkin Rings make perfect wedding gifts.
You've been living under a rock if you didn't know that Moroccan Poufs are hot right now. Serving as a foot stool, side table, or extra seating, they're not only stylish but useful.

Think you'd never hear affordable midcentury modern in the same sentence? Well here it is. This side table is handcrafted, made from more economical materials. Luckily, the plywood is pre-finished with a durable material that will provide a trouble free surface for a long time. So, now you just have to find your Don Draper.

Want that midcentury modern look, without the steep price tag? The triangle stand is perfect. It shows some character... because not all tables have to be round or square. Made with economical material (plywood surface and solid ash legs), it exhibits the same craftsmanship of a solid wood piece.
A nod to '40s Chinoiserie but updated for today. 100% cotton velvet upholstery. It brings a touch of hollywood glam to any room. Go ahead, summon your inner Audrey Hepburn.
Place it on the table or floor. The golden poodle is a beautiful accent for any room. Perfect if you're going for the glam or contemporary look. It's the dog you wanted, without the morning walks.
This lamp was inspired by a well-timed drive through Mexico’s Michoacán region during the breathtaking butterfly season. It's gorgeous. We're getting butterflies just thinking about it.
Stunning, low profile swivel chair with blue velvet upholstery and metal structure. It's sure to turn heads.

We're loving leopard-print! Although it seems like an inherently rule-breaking decorating choice, it does abide by a few rules, number one being that it looks amazing paired with chic touches of black and metal. Go ahead, give it a try.

A Mid-Century Modern dresser by Broyhill. This classically styled dresser is just the piece for your home. With 6 sturdy, deep drawers built of solid wood there is plenty of storage to go around. Still as handsome as ever and ready to handle anything you can toss at it.

By mid-century Scandinavian pottery studio Sejer, this phenomenal lamp emits a dazzling chiaroscuro pattern from its lava-like surface. Beautiful earthtones with touches of white glaze. Rare and highly collectible. Denmark, 1960s.
Now you know what all the buzz is about... this beautifully crafted bookcase made with hexagonal honeycomb cells. The image doesn't quite to the size and stature of this piece justice.
This hand-crafted piece was built from exotic demolition hardwoods. It features a patchwork surface, balancing urban aesthetic with sustainable design. You can't get cooler than that.
The Quinn chair caught our eye because its got that 'flea market find' feel. Comfortable seating with a buttery top grain leather. Now, that's our definition of fine dining.
You don't need to turn this lamp on for it to shine! We love the distressed gold finish. It offers warmth and a bit of shine without being over the top.
Did we make you stop in your tracks? This railroad light is a bold piece. If you're a daring individual that likes to weave 'out of the box' decor seamlessly into a room, this has your name on it
The Chesterfield has remained a classic style over the years. It's intrinsically luxurious. The distressed leather adds age, wisdom, and a bit of chic.
What a classy little perch! This velvet barrel chair has beautiful tufted detail and a soft and soothing grey fabric.

The bright green bungee cords that form the structure of this chair caught our attention in store. Although some may say this desk chair is fairly standard in its look, we argue that its price tag makes it a steal.
Vintage brass regency lamp table with wood greek column legs and heavy brass base. Detailed brass frame topped with beveled glass insert and wood edge. Very unique style table.

A stunning piece of art! Large pace brass coffee table circa 1970. Heavy beveled glass top with glass cube enclosed with heavy brass corners and hardware. Good condition with very minor chip on one edge of glass.

Rare & beautiful, this is the holy grail chinoiserie find! This vintage wrought iron patio set attributed to Woodard Co. circa 1950. It has Greek key detailing and thick heavy wrought iron construction. Features original paint. If you would like a new coat of lacquer we can arrange for this. Good condition for age & use. Comes with 2 Arm Chairs: 26"W x 16"D x 33"H, and 4 Side Chairs: 18"W x 16"D x 33"H
fields.short_name: Wrought Iron Greek Key Patio Set

fields.description: Mid century modern side tables with front doors and storage. Rare hexagonal shape finished in white lacquer by local artist. Stunning look with detailed fretwork on front doors. Excellent condition. Circa 1975

A rare pair of midcentury modern, lounge low boy chairs on casters. These low slung chairs look like they're right out of Elvis' dressing room. Made of tufted black naugahyde, they have the retro, gangster look. Circa 1950's and in excellent condition. Like the clean lines sitting on round wood legs.

MCM Style chrome chaise lounge attributed to Le Corbusier finished in chrome with black padding and round pillow. Excellent condition, does not have a stand. Circa 1980's purchased from a San Francisco estate. Le Corbusier designed this famous chair in 1928 and is a piece of post modern art. This lounge is permanently displayed at the Museum of Modern Art in New York. This item requires delivery using a trusted freight carrier

Mid Century Modern chest attributed to Dorothy Draper finished in a black lacquer with a geometric pattern with gold & brass pulls. Rare piece of mcm art circa 1950's. Good condition with very minor chips and scratches. The top was recently re-lacquered.

Very highly detailed carved wooden headboard with gilt finish. Can be used as a room divider, valence panel, or as wall or entry decor.  Large, beautiful, and in excellent condition. Looks even more intricate and beautiful in person.

Vintage row of oak folding theater chairs from Alameda Country School District in California. Rich, warm finish on the solid wood row. Strong & stable quality construction circa 1920's. Folds completely flat. Graceful, curving legs and back rests with an aged patina. Adds fun, function, and nostalgia to your space.

From the Qing Dynasty era -- yeah, it's old (estimated circa 1860). This is a rare antique Chinese hardwood three section desk. The entire desk is made with mortise and tenon joints and comes apart in three sections (with two towers, each with two drawers and a door). Beautiful hardware and lock plates. very good condition with minor scratches.

Like we said, the furniture hunt is over. But, if you're still in the mood for a safari, here are some beautiful Mid-Century Modern safari lounge chairs by Maurice Burke. They have been professionally reupholstered in black leather. Two available ($1,000 each). Great condition with minor vintage wear.
Unique chest with upper and lower cabinets, two doors each, with latches. Metal strapping and rosette details.
If you're into the industrial look, this is the perfect piece. Unique spool shape and beautiful patina on the brass. Circa 1950's

Greeting you with arms wide open, the curves of this chair resemble the petals of a flower. Circa 1960s. Made of lacquered metal and black wicker. Good condition with very minimal loss of wicker (does not affect the structural integrity of the piece).

We love this look. 4 gorgeous chairs full of unusual shapes and curves (it's flattering if you say it about furniture). Nothing obvious. Accented by the shield back with an intriguing pattern of welded spirals. c1930.
fields.short_name: Art Deco Wrought Iron Patio Chairs

fields.description: A charming and stylish art deco end table of unknown origins. Constructed of solid wood. Newly refinished.
Double pedestal base coffee table with multiple strands stacked for each pedestal. Faux finish, 1940′s wood grain laminate top.
This is a must have if you want to mix things up a bit in your space. The base of this lamp is made from a 1935 sunbeam appliance.
Made from an 1890's Universal No. 1 meat grinder by L.F.& C. in new Britain, Conn.
Reclaimed Douglas Fir workshop table and repurposed steel park bench frame. Wood finished with teak oil and metal finished with satin clear coat.

2.5 seat sofa with solid Tasmanian Oak frame, galvanized hardware and green line Italian Pirelli webbing. Feather / Fiber cushioning. Fully upholstered with timber and metal detailed feet. Made in Australia.
Inspired by the shape of wind-filled sails and designed by the Dutch company Montis, this chair is so smooth.
This lightweight and compact chair is a counterpoint to the Fauteuil grand confort, more massive, and it is in perfect balance with the table in steel tube and the chaiselongue.
This 2-door wardrobe has a presence. It's strong stature is nicely balanced by its crackle finish. We wonder if these doors lead to Narnia.

We admit it. These lamps reminded us of creamsicles. Given that association, they are hard to resist. From a style standpoint, these lamps could be a great accent to a room ruled by white and neutral. Only $155 for the pair.
The natural character of the pine stands out in these 1-door side tables. They have a nice rustic feel. 2 available.
This is one handsome Hi-Boy. It's got all the right lines, like any great midcentury modern piece should. It's sure to sweep you away, especially with its sea green color.
Tufted? Pink? Velvet? It's the triple threat. What else do you need to know? Oh, yes, it's $205 for the set of 4.
Moroccan-style furniture is all the rage right now... and it's easy to see why. We're easily seduced by the shapes and mosaics.

A slim profile loaded with handcrafted details that include thick, comfortable padding, a blue damask front with covered button accent and gently curved birch legs. Who knew that even chairs can never be too thin or too rich? (piece was exclusively made for Pier 1)

Whenever we think vintage school desk, we can't help but think Little House on the Prairie. Now, this piece may not be as old, but it still has a lot of character. Repainted in a calming Sea Foam Green.

Characterized by its sleek styling and quality construction, Lane Furniture has been an iconic American brand since 1912. It is a key name when it comes to mid-century modern furniture. These Lane side tables are $150 each.
This piece can function as a side table or your kitchen bar.We like it because it doesn't look to shiny and manufactured or over-the-top. Solid.

fields.description: Nice and simple, mid-century modern dining table. It has gorgeous splayed legs and a beautiful teak grain. Handcrafted and made from reclaimed wood.

fields.terms: $10 off your first order up to $50 total
fields.name: 10% Off First Order

fields.description: Leftovers will make you swoon! Receiving 3-5 deliveries a day, you never know what vintage gems will come in through the door. If you're looking for unique and ever-changing eye candy, Leftovers in the place!

Past Perfect is a world renowned antique, vintage and modern collective. Operated by 30 plus independent dealers, you're sure to find something special. Past Perfect carries a range of items, from mid-century modern to antique. New items arrive daily.

Cavalier is a destination for seekers of all that is uncommon and collected. True to a code that celebrates all that is singular and luxurious, Cavalier showcases carefully curated new, vintage and bespoke pieces. It is the exclusive source for interior designer Jay Jeffers’ debut collection of California‐made furniture, as well as the sole stockist for a limited‐edition selection of home furnishings and accessories created in partnership with designers from around the world.

This store was made for home decor addicts. Stop by and see their ever changing room displays, updated daily. You'll truly find one-of-a-kind inspiration for your room or a solution to any design challenge.

Harrington Galleries is a lifestyle emporium has been a Bay Area landmark for more than 40 years. Specializing in estate liquidation, they sell antiques and vintage furniture. These items are complimented by carefully selected new furniture items... mixing the best of the old with the best of the new.

Big Daddy’s Antiques is a retailer of one-of-a-kind antiques and reproductions from European, Asian, and North American markets. Whether you are looking for that funky one-of-a-kind antique piece, looking to create your own unique piece, or seeking an eclectic location for your next event, Big Daddy’s is the place to be.

Every piece we find is a chance to learn about and appreciate a designer or artist that created a beautiful moment in history - moments that we can all fill our homes and work spaces with to create environments full of sculptural lines, rich tones, and unique details

The name Ohmega is derived from the greek symbol omega, signifying rebirth, and 'ohm's law', the measure of electrical resistance. Ohmega Salvage  builds community through commerce by being a model of reuse, recycling and social exchange.

Zinc Details is an independently owned showroom, gallery, modern design authority and essential resource for the San Francisco creative community since 1991. Zinc Details assembles an exuberant mix of art, design and craft that is expertly curated from sources around the globe.
Carousel Consignment has a love and flair for circus and all things vintage. They have collected vintage/antique furniture, art, and decor for years, with a fervor bordering on obsession.
